    "Inconsistent, incomplete, or inaccurate data can lead to unreliable predictions and insights, potentially compromising food safety.",
    "For example, missing or erroneous sensor data can affect real-time monitoring and control systems, leading to undetected temperature deviations.",
    "(2) Algorithm limitations: AI algorithms, including those used in predictive analytics, image recognition, and anomaly detection, have inherent limitations [240].",
    "For instance, ML models may struggle to generalize from training data to real-world scenarios, leading to reduced performance in detecting new or unforeseen types of defects and contaminants.",
